    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P26"><text:a xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="https://ro.wikisource.org/wiki/O_scrisoare_pierdut#cite_ref-4" text:style-name="Internet_20_link" text:visited-style-name="Visited_20_Internet_20_Link"><text:span text:style-name="T9"></text:span></text:a><text:span text:style-name="T7"></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T5">Corespunde preceptului biblic: Cine are urechi de auzit s aud!</text:span></text:p>
    </text:list-item>
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P26"><text:a xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="https://ro.wikisource.org/wiki/O_scrisoare_pierdut#cite_ref-5" text:style-name="Internet_20_link" text:visited-style-name="Visited_20_Internet_20_Link"><text:span text:style-name="T9"></text:span></text:a><text:span text:style-name="T7"></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T5">Confuzie, ilustrnd preteniile de cultur ale lui Caavencu. Formula aparine, de fapt, lui Machiavelli. Gambetta, om politic francez chiar din acea vreme, era ns mai cunoscut eroilor lui Caragiale.</text:span></text:p>
